Public hospitals in Nyeri county were deserted yesterday as the health workers strike entered the second day.Most public hospitals' wards were empty.At the the Nyeri Referral Hospital, relatives were seen transferring their patients to private health facilities.Patient Joyce Muthoni from Endarasha said she had to transfer her son to a private hospital in Mweiga town after the health workers downed their tools on Monday.&ldquo;My son has been admitted here for five months. I don&rsquo;t know where I will get money to pay for such expensive hospitals,&rdquo; she said.Another patient was seen crying inside an ambulance after the strike.Local private hospitals cashed-in as more and more patients continued to seek medical attention.